					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Agadat ha-Talmud, a collection of hagadot occuring in the Talmud.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="tmr" otherLangs="he">Aramaic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="140v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Agadat ha-Talmud</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אגדת התלמוד</title>
							<note>
								<p>Folios 1r-13v contain an index of the Biblical passages referred to in the body of the work. Probably two leaves are missing at the beginning.</p>
								<p>Folio 13v contains a list of masekhtot referred to in the text.</p>
								<p>Folios 14r-19v come from another collection of agadot from the tractate Berakhot. </p>
								<p>The work proper begins on folio 20r.</p>
								<p>Berakhot here is treated as a part of Seder Mo῾ed; the tractate Shabat follows Berakhot as part of the same Seder.</p>
								<p>Seder Nashim begins on folio 63r, Seder Yeshu῾ot (Neziḳin) on folio 86r, and Seder Ḳodashim on folio 130r.</p>
								<p>Seder Ṭoharot is, in the present condition of the manuscript, not represented at all.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Yemenite square and semi-cursive script of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
